{
  "total_duration": 796.967,
  "lines": [
    {
      "i": 0,
      "start": 0.0,
      "end": 6.264,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "hook",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "今天的题目是"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "Do you call that a hat?"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "，中文是“你把那个叫帽子吗？”"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 1,
      "start": 6.614,
      "end": 16.374,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "hook",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "先说清楚，这不是一课嘲笑帽子，也不是嘲笑谁爱买东西。它是一场 shopping taste comedy，购物审美冲突喜剧。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 2,
      "start": 16.724,
      "end": 24.267,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "hook",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "课文里的"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "hat shop"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "不是随便买一顶 baseball cap 的小摊，而是专门卖帽子的店。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 3,
      "start": 24.617,
      "end": 36.457,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "hook",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "在过去的英国和欧洲，帽子常常是 formal dress 的一部分。婚礼、教堂、赛马会、花园聚会、正式场合，都可能要戴一顶讲究的帽子。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 4,
      "start": 36.807,
      "end": 44.887,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "hook",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "所以妻子在镜子前看很久，并不是只为了遮太阳，而是在挑一件 fashion statement，一件表达审美和场合的配饰。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 5,
      "start": 45.237,
      "end": 50.861,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "hook",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "这时候丈夫等得不耐烦，开口说："
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "Do you call that a hat?"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 6,
      "start": 51.211,
      "end": 56.771,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "hook",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "注意，这不是 neutral question。它真正的语气是：这也能叫帽子？"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 7,
      "start": 57.121,
      "end": 64.385,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "hook",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "这种句子在故事里有喜剧效果，但现实里直接说给别人听，会很"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "rude"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 8,
      "start": 64.734,
      "end": 73.814,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "hook",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "更好笑的是，丈夫批评妻子的帽子，可他自己昨天刚买了一条 terrible tie。最后妻子用他的领带反击。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 9,
      "start": 74.164,
      "end": 94.844,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "hook",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "整课记忆链是：hat shop -> mirror -> Do you call that a hat -> needn't be so rude -> modern chair with holes -> half an hour -> mustn't buy things we don't need -> needn't have said that -> terrible tie -> too many ties -> too many hats -> lighthouse hat。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 10,
      "start": 95.194,
      "end": 103.458,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "retell",
      "scene_meta": {
        "frame": "1"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "第一幅画，是 rude opening。课文开头就是一句："
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "'Do you call that a hat?' I said to my wife."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 11,
      "start": 103.808,
      "end": 110.576,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "retell",
      "scene_meta": {
        "frame": "1"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "wife"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "是妻子，the narrator's spouse。她正在帽店里试帽子。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 12,
      "start": 110.926,
      "end": 117.59,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "retell",
      "scene_meta": {
        "frame": "1"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "她回答："
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "'You needn't be so rude about it,' my wife answered as she looked at herself in the mirror."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 13,
      "start": 117.94,
      "end": 126.828,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "retell",
      "scene_meta": {
        "frame": "1"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "looked at herself in the mirror"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "是照镜子看自己。她不是在发呆，而是在认真判断这顶帽子合不合适。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 14,
      "start": 127.177,
      "end": 136.769,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "retell",
      "scene_meta": {
        "frame": "1"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "Needn't"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "的意思是 don't need to，没有必要。"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "You needn't be so rude"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "就是：你没必要这样不客气。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 15,
      "start": 137.119,
      "end": 145.459,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "retell",
      "scene_meta": {
        "frame": "1"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "这一幅要记住：他的问题听起来像玩笑，其实很直接；她的反应很清楚：Please speak more politely."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 16,
      "start": 145.809,
      "end": 153.961,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "retell",
      "scene_meta": {
        "frame": "2"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "第二幅画，是 waiting chair。课文说："
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "I sat down on one of those modern chairs with holes in it and waited."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 17,
      "start": 154.311,
      "end": 164.118,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "retell",
      "scene_meta": {
        "frame": "2"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "modern chair"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "是新式椅子；"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "holes"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "是洞或者网眼。这里的椅子很有时代感，也有一点滑稽。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 18,
      "start": 164.468,
      "end": 171.228,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "retell",
      "scene_meta": {
        "frame": "2"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "接着课文说："
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "We had been in the hat shop for half an hour and my wife was still in front of the mirror."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 19,
      "start": 171.578,
      "end": 179.306,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "retell",
      "scene_meta": {
        "frame": "2"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "Half an hour"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "是三十分钟。"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "still in front of the mirror"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "表示她还站在镜子前。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 20,
      "start": 179.656,
      "end": 186.296,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "retell",
      "scene_meta": {
        "frame": "2"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "这不是说她 foolish，而是让你感到丈夫为什么越来越 impatient。他已经坐下等了很久。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 21,
      "start": 186.646,
      "end": 195.686,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "retell",
      "scene_meta": {
        "frame": "2"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "今天也一样：有人试衣服、鞋子、眼镜、手机壳，另一个人在旁边等，审美差异就可能开始冒出来。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 22,
      "start": 196.036,
      "end": 204.371,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "retell",
      "scene_meta": {
        "frame": "3"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "第三幅画，是 the careless rule。丈夫突然说："
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "'We mustn't buy things we don't need,' I remarked suddenly."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 23,
      "start": 204.721,
      "end": 215.285,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "retell",
      "scene_meta": {
        "frame": "3"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "Mustn't"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "比"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "needn't"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "强，意思是 must not，不能、不应该，像一条规则。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 24,
      "start": 215.635,
      "end": 223.315,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "retell",
      "scene_meta": {
        "frame": "3"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "他表面上是在说“不要买不需要的东西”，但在这个场景里，听起来就是在批评妻子的帽子。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 25,
      "start": 223.665,
      "end": 228.473,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "retell",
      "scene_meta": {
        "frame": "3"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "所以课文马上说："
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "I regretted saying it almost at once."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 26,
      "start": 228.823,
      "end": 237.374,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "retell",
      "scene_meta": {
        "frame": "3"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "Regretted"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "是后悔；"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "almost at once"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "是几乎立刻。他一说出口，就知道坏了。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 27,
      "start": 237.724,
      "end": 241.1,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "retell",
      "scene_meta": {
        "frame": "3"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "妻子回答："
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "'You needn't have said that.'"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 28,
      "start": 241.45,
      "end": 249.246,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "retell",
      "scene_meta": {
        "frame": "3"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "这是今天最尖的小语法："
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "needn't have said"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "。意思是：你已经说了，但那句话本来没必要说。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 29,
      "start": 249.596,
      "end": 255.252,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "retell",
      "scene_meta": {
        "frame": "3"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "然后她拿出反击："
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "'I needn't remind you of that terrible tie you bought yesterday.'"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 30,
      "start": 255.602,
      "end": 265.233,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "retell",
      "scene_meta": {
        "frame": "3"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "Remind"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "是提醒、让人想起。她是在说：你也有自己的 questionable taste，别只批评我的帽子。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 31,
      "start": 265.583,
      "end": 273.327,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "retell",
      "scene_meta": {
        "frame": "4"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "第四幅画，是 lighthouse ending。丈夫还想防守："
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "'I find it beautiful,' I said."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 32,
      "start": 273.677,
      "end": 280.181,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "retell",
      "scene_meta": {
        "frame": "4"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "I find it beautiful"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "的意思是 I think it is beautiful，我觉得它很好看。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 33,
      "start": 280.531,
      "end": 284.771,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "retell",
      "scene_meta": {
        "frame": "4"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "然后他说："
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "'A man can never have too many ties.'"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 34,
      "start": 285.121,
      "end": 290.161,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "retell",
      "scene_meta": {
        "frame": "4"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "这是一句 comic exaggeration，夸张说法：领带再多也不嫌多。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 35,
      "start": 290.511,
      "end": 296.606,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "retell",
      "scene_meta": {
        "frame": "4"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "妻子立刻对称反击："
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "'And a woman can't have too many hats,' she answered."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 36,
      "start": 296.956,
      "end": 306.196,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "retell",
      "scene_meta": {
        "frame": "4"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "注意，这不是要教你“男人一定爱领带、女人一定爱帽子”。这是 old-style comic symmetry，一种老式对称笑点。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 37,
      "start": 306.546,
      "end": 314.346,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "retell",
      "scene_meta": {
        "frame": "4"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "现代一点说就是：你有你的收藏，我有我的审美。你觉得你的东西值得买，我也可以觉得我的东西值得买。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 38,
      "start": 314.696,
      "end": 319.656,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "retell",
      "scene_meta": {
        "frame": "4"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "最后课文说："
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "Ten minutes later we walked out of the shop together."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 39,
      "start": 320.006,
      "end": 324.23,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "retell",
      "scene_meta": {
        "frame": "4"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "My wife was wearing a hat that looked like a lighthouse!"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 40,
      "start": 324.58,
      "end": 332.804,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "retell",
      "scene_meta": {
        "frame": "4"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "Lighthouse"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "是海边给船指路的灯塔。帽子像灯塔，说明它很高、很显眼、很 dramatic。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 41,
      "start": 333.154,
      "end": 339.714,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "retell",
      "scene_meta": {
        "frame": "4"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "结尾的笑点是：他批评她的帽子，可她用他的领带赢回了这场小辩论。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 42,
      "start": 340.063,
      "end": 341.683,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "discuss",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "这一课最容易误会什么？"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 43,
      "start": 342.033,
      "end": 345.709,
      "speaker": "B",
      "scene": "discuss",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "以为是在笑妻子买帽子，或者笑女生购物？"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 44,
      "start": 346.059,
      "end": 353.379,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "discuss",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "对，所以我们要把 tone 放正。妻子不是 silly。她在正式帽店里认真挑一顶 dramatic formal hat。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 45,
      "start": 353.729,
      "end": 356.951,
      "speaker": "B",
      "scene": "discuss",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "那丈夫呢？他是坏人吗？"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 46,
      "start": 357.3,
      "end": 366.644,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "discuss",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "也不是。他等了半个小时，累了，不耐烦了。但他的语言太直接，所以听起来"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "rude"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 47,
      "start": 366.994,
      "end": 371.118,
      "speaker": "B",
      "scene": "discuss",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "Do you call that a hat?"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "为什么这么 rude？"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 48,
      "start": 371.468,
      "end": 383.048,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "discuss",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "因为它不是问信息，而是在否定对方的选择。像"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "Do you call that music?"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "或"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "Do you call that a plan?"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "，语气都很讽刺。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 49,
      "start": 383.398,
      "end": 388.943,
      "speaker": "B",
      "scene": "discuss",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "那"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "We mustn't buy things we don't need"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "听起来是不是挺合理？"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 50,
      "start": 389.293,
      "end": 398.893,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "discuss",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "内容可能合理，但 timing 很危险。别人正在试一件自己喜欢的东西，你突然把它叫作 unnecessary，就像把审美变成了批评。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 51,
      "start": 399.242,
      "end": 401.704,
      "speaker": "B",
      "scene": "discuss",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "妻子的 comeback 为什么有效？"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 52,
      "start": 402.054,
      "end": 411.854,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "discuss",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "因为她提醒他：你昨天也买了一条我觉得 terrible 的 tie。你可以为自己的 taste 辩护，那我也可以为我的 hat 辩护。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 53,
      "start": 412.204,
      "end": 414.329,
      "speaker": "B",
      "scene": "discuss",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "所以重点不是谁赢？"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 54,
      "start": 414.679,
      "end": 422.159,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "discuss",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "对，重点是 disagreement can be polite。你可以不喜欢别人的选择，但不用让对方难堪。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 55,
      "start": 422.509,
      "end": 426.853,
      "speaker": "B",
      "scene": "passage_normal",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "'Do you call that a hat?' I said to my wife."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 56,
      "start": 427.203,
      "end": 432.267,
      "speaker": "B",
      "scene": "passage_normal",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "'You needn't be so rude about it,' my wife answered as she looked at herself in the mirror."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 57,
      "start": 432.617,
      "end": 436.865,
      "speaker": "B",
      "scene": "passage_normal",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "I sat down on one of those modern chairs with holes in it and waited."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 58,
      "start": 437.214,
      "end": 442.23,
      "speaker": "B",
      "scene": "passage_normal",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "We had been in the hat shop for half an hour and my wife was still in front of the mirror."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 59,
      "start": 442.58,
      "end": 446.492,
      "speaker": "B",
      "scene": "passage_normal",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "'We mustn't buy things we don't need,' I remarked suddenly."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 60,
      "start": 446.842,
      "end": 449.986,
      "speaker": "B",
      "scene": "passage_normal",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "I regretted saying it almost at once."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 61,
      "start": 450.336,
      "end": 453.528,
      "speaker": "B",
      "scene": "passage_normal",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "'You needn't have said that,' my wife answered."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 62,
      "start": 453.878,
      "end": 457.934,
      "speaker": "B",
      "scene": "passage_normal",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "'I needn't remind you of that terrible tie you bought yesterday.'"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 63,
      "start": 458.284,
      "end": 461.02,
      "speaker": "B",
      "scene": "passage_normal",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "'I find it beautiful,' I said."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 64,
      "start": 461.37,
      "end": 464.442,
      "speaker": "B",
      "scene": "passage_normal",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "'A man can never have too many ties.'"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 65,
      "start": 464.792,
      "end": 468.536,
      "speaker": "B",
      "scene": "passage_normal",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "'And a woman can't have too many hats,' she answered."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 66,
      "start": 468.885,
      "end": 472.413,
      "speaker": "B",
      "scene": "passage_normal",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "Ten minutes later we walked out of the shop together."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 67,
      "start": 472.763,
      "end": 476.603,
      "speaker": "B",
      "scene": "passage_normal",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "My wife was wearing a hat that looked like a lighthouse!"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 68,
      "start": 476.953,
      "end": 479.497,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "vocab",
      "scene_meta": {
        "word": "rude"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "第一个词："
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "rude"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 69,
      "start": 479.847,
      "end": 481.311,
      "speaker": "B",
      "scene": "vocab",
      "scene_meta": {
        "word": "rude"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "rude"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 70,
      "start": 481.661,
      "end": 489.965,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "vocab",
      "scene_meta": {
        "word": "rude"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "Rude"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "means not polite，not kind in the way you speak or behave。不礼貌，容易让人受伤或难堪。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 71,
      "start": 490.315,
      "end": 494.611,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "vocab",
      "scene_meta": {
        "word": "rude"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "课文里妻子说："
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "You needn't be so rude about it."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 72,
      "start": 494.96,
      "end": 502.2,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "vocab",
      "scene_meta": {
        "word": "rude"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "她不是说丈夫不能有意见。她是在说：You do not need to say it in such a sharp way."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 73,
      "start": 502.55,
      "end": 511.754,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "vocab",
      "scene_meta": {
        "word": "rude"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "所以"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "rude"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "的重点不只是内容，也包括 tone。直说“这也能叫帽子？”就太刺了。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 74,
      "start": 512.104,
      "end": 514.856,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "vocab",
      "scene_meta": {
        "word": "remind"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "第二个词："
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "remind"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 75,
      "start": 515.206,
      "end": 516.886,
      "speaker": "B",
      "scene": "vocab",
      "scene_meta": {
        "word": "remind"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "remind"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 76,
      "start": 517.236,
      "end": 524.348,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "vocab",
      "scene_meta": {
        "word": "remind"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "Remind"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "means make someone remember something，提醒，让某人想起某事。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 77,
      "start": 524.698,
      "end": 529.693,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "vocab",
      "scene_meta": {
        "word": "remind"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "课文说："
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "I needn't remind you of that terrible tie you bought yesterday."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 78,
      "start": 530.043,
      "end": 536.683,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "vocab",
      "scene_meta": {
        "word": "remind"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "妻子不是真的忘不了那条 tie。她是在提醒丈夫：你昨天也买了一个我觉得不好看的东西。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 79,
      "start": 537.033,
      "end": 544.537,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "vocab",
      "scene_meta": {
        "word": "remind"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "Remind someone of something"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "是很常用的搭配。这里的 reminder 让丈夫的批评变得 less convincing。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 80,
      "start": 544.887,
      "end": 547.831,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "vocab",
      "scene_meta": {
        "word": "lighthouse"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "第三个词："
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "lighthouse"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 81,
      "start": 548.181,
      "end": 549.909,
      "speaker": "B",
      "scene": "vocab",
      "scene_meta": {
        "word": "lighthouse"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "lighthouse"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 82,
      "start": 550.259,
      "end": 558.803,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "vocab",
      "scene_meta": {
        "word": "lighthouse"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "Lighthouse"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "is a tall tower near the sea with a light that guides ships，海边给船指路的灯塔。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 83,
      "start": 559.152,
      "end": 564.496,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "vocab",
      "scene_meta": {
        "word": "lighthouse"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "课文最后说："
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "My wife was wearing a hat that looked like a lighthouse!"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 84,
      "start": 564.846,
      "end": 571.726,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "vocab",
      "scene_meta": {
        "word": "lighthouse"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "这不是说她真的把灯塔戴在头上，而是说那顶帽子 tall, noticeable, and dramatic。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 85,
      "start": 572.076,
      "end": 579.156,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "vocab",
      "scene_meta": {
        "word": "lighthouse"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "这个词把结尾一下子变成画面：帽子高高的、很显眼，像正式帽子被推到喜剧极限。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 86,
      "start": 579.506,
      "end": 584.026,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "grammar",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "今天的 grammar 不要背散点，要放在这场购物争论里听。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 87,
      "start": 584.376,
      "end": 590.852,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "grammar",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "第一组："
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "needn't"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "。它等于"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "don't need to"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "，没有必要。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 88,
      "start": 591.201,
      "end": 598.097,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "grammar",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "妻子说："
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "You needn't be so rude about it."
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "意思是：你没必要用这么不礼貌的方式说。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 89,
      "start": 598.447,
      "end": 606.111,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "grammar",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "第二组："
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "mustn't"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "。它等于"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "must not"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "，更强，像规则或警告。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 90,
      "start": 606.461,
      "end": 613.492,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "grammar",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "丈夫说："
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "We mustn't buy things we don't need."
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "意思是：我们不应该买不需要的东西。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 91,
      "start": 613.842,
      "end": 618.962,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "grammar",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "但是在帽店里，这句话听起来像 criticism，所以他马上后悔。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 92,
      "start": 619.312,
      "end": 626.192,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "grammar",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "第三组："
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "needn't have done"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "。这是说：事情已经做了，但本来没必要做。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 93,
      "start": 626.542,
      "end": 629.798,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "grammar",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "妻子说："
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "You needn't have said that."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 94,
      "start": 630.148,
      "end": 637.828,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "grammar",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "这句话很关键：He already said it. He cannot pull it back. She means that sentence was unnecessary."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 95,
      "start": 638.178,
      "end": 648.409,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "grammar",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "再听一遍对比："
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "You needn't be so rude."
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "现在没必要这样说；"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "You needn't have said that."
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "刚才那句话本来没必要说。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 96,
      "start": 648.759,
      "end": 653.247,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "grammar",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "最后还有一句喜剧公式："
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "can never have too many"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 97,
      "start": 653.597,
      "end": 660.757,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "grammar",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "A man can never have too many ties."
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "是夸张地说，领带再多也不嫌多。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 98,
      "start": 661.107,
      "end": 667.703,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "grammar",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "妻子把公式换成"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "A woman can't have too many hats."
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "，于是反击完成。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 99,
      "start": 668.052,
      "end": 680.116,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "grammar",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "板书可以记成：polite disagreement = soften your words；rule language ="
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "mustn't"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "；past regret ="
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "needn't have said"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 100,
      "start": 680.466,
      "end": 685.466,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "you_too",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "现在把这课放进你的生活。想象你和朋友或家人一起 shopping。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 101,
      "start": 685.816,
      "end": 694.496,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "you_too",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "对方选了一顶很夸张的帽子，也可能是一件外套、一个 phone case、一双 sneakers，或者一个 collectible figure。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 102,
      "start": 694.846,
      "end": 701.47,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "you_too",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "你不喜欢，但你不想说"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "Do you call that a hat?"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "这种很刺的话。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 103,
      "start": 701.82,
      "end": 707.499,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "you_too",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "可以先说柔和一点："
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "It is not really my style, but you can try it on."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 104,
      "start": 707.849,
      "end": 714.561,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "you_too",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "如果要说规则，可以用"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "mustn't"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "："
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "We mustn't spend more than our budget."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 105,
      "start": 714.911,
      "end": 722.583,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "you_too",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "如果你刚才说得太直接，可以道歉："
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "Sorry. I needn't have said it so directly."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 106,
      "start": 722.933,
      "end": 728.325,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "you_too",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "如果对方担心你的意见，可以说："
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "You needn't worry about my opinion."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 107,
      "start": 728.675,
      "end": 735.095,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "you_too",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "今天的生活技能不是 pretend to like everything，而是 disagree without humiliating someone。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 108,
      "start": 735.444,
      "end": 747.544,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "you_too",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "这道练习要你补完整一段 polite shopping talk，用"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "needn't"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "、"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "mustn't"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "和"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "needn't have said"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "把话说得更稳。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
